headline: Is It Too Late To Consider RTX (RTX) After Its Strong Multi Year Share Price Run
summary: If you are wondering whether RTX at US$195.93 still makes sense on a valuation basis after its strong run, this article will walk through what the numbers are actually saying about the current price. The stock has seen a 3.0% decline over the last 7 days, a 5.8% gain over 30 days, a 4.6% gain year to date, a 59.3% gain over 1 year and a 110.5% gain over 3 years, with a very large gain over 5 years that is a little more than 3x the 5 year starting point. These moves sit alongside ongoing news...

headline: Bloom Energy, Lumentum, and Other Hot Stocks Set up for Earnings Beats
summary: Which companies are most likely to beat Wall Street profit forecasts?  Investors can get a big clue by looking at recent changes to a key metric: the price-to-earnings ratios.  When it comes to picking stocks, conventional wisdom holds that low price-to-earnings ratios are an advantage.
